      "content": "i mean i get the functional part, but why go to all that trouble for just traffic flow? it feels way too intentional. like, if you trace the ley lines through the diagonal avenues, they don't just connect points, they create a sort of star-like structure that's centered right where the power is. it's not just \"urban ideals,\" it feels like they were trying to anchor something to the ground. don't you think the math behind those specific intersections is a bit too perfect to be just about movement?",
